--> https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/linux
--> sudo snap install flutter --classic --> run this command
--> flutter doctor --> run this it shows required files 
--> https://developer.android.com/studio?gclid=EAIaIQobChMI5LTouImEggMVWXErCh2BBQ-iEAAYASAAEgJYgvD_BwE&gclsrc=aw.ds
--> download Android studio for linux
--> extract file
--> open studio.sh in terminal
--> run ./studio.sh in terminal
--> it will launch A  ndroid studio
--> In Android studio Tools-> SDK manager-> Android SDK-> select required Android studio version->apply->ok
--> Then create one folder in home using terminal -> mkdir Flutter -> cd Flutter/
--> flutter create learningdart --> this will create flutter project called "learningdart"
--> cd learningdart/
--> code . --> to launch VsCode
--> then start working
---------------------
NOTE:
--> In VsCode "ctrl + p" to select which application to be launched (eg, web, desktop etc)

